# AQI Early Warning System — India

Predicts Air Quality Index (AQI) up to 7 days ahead for 26 Indian cities using
machine learning, with automated health advisories and a live web dashboard.

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| 7-day AQI forecast | LSTM time-series model predicts next 7 days numerically |
| Multi-model comparison | Random Forest vs XGBoost — best model auto-selected |
| SMOTE | Handles class imbalance for rare Severe/Very Poor days |
| SHAP explainability | Shows which pollutant drove each prediction |
| Health advisory | Auto-generated advisory text per AQI level |
| Population alerts | Tailored advice for children, elderly, asthma, healthy adults |
| Activity recommender | Safe/Avoid for jogging, school sports, cycling, outdoor dining |
| Spike anomaly detection | Flags sudden AQI spikes using rolling Z-score |
| Festival awareness | Alerts for Diwali / crop-burning season (Oct–Nov) |
| Live API data | Real-time pollutant readings via OpenWeatherMap |
| City vs city compare | Side-by-side 7-day forecast for two cities |
| Confidence score | Prediction probability breakdown across all 6 AQI categories |

---

## Setup

```

### 2. Download dataset
- Go to: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rohanrao/air-quality-data-in-india
- Download `city_day.csv`
- Place it in the `data/` folder

### 3. Add your API key (optional — for live data)
Create a `.env` file in the project root:
```
OWM_API_KEY=58512efcd478bf101f6d4849ac7de2f4


```
Get a free key at: https://openweathermap.org/api/air-pollution

### 4. Train the models
```bash
python train.py

run :
C:\Users\inert\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python310\python.exe train.py
```
This takes 5–15 minutes depending on your machine.
Saves trained models to `models/` and plots to `plots/`.

### 5. Launch the dashboard
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```
Opens at http://localhost:8501

---

## Tech Stack

- **pandas, numpy** — data processing
- **scikit-learn** — Random Forest, preprocessing, metrics
- **XGBoost** — gradient boosted classifier
- **TensorFlow/Keras** — LSTM time-series model
- **imbalanced-learn** — SMOTE oversampling
- **SHAP** — model explainability
- **Streamlit** — web dashboard
- **Plotly** — interactive charts
- **requests** — live API integration

---

## Project Structure

```
aqi-early-warning/
├── data/
│   └── city_day.csv
├── models/              ← auto-generated by train.py
│   ├── classifier.pkl
│   ├── lstm_model.keras
│   ├── scaler.pkl
│   └── ...
├── plots/               ← auto-generated by train.py
├── train.py             ← ML training pipeline
├── app.py               ← Streamlit dashboard
├── advisory.py          ← health advisory engine
├── live_api.py          ← OpenWeatherMap integration
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## Dataset

**India Air Quality Data** — Rohan Rao, Kaggle  
26 cities | 2015–2020 | Daily readings  
Features: PM2.5, PM10, NO, NO2, NOx, NH3, CO, SO2, O3, Benzene, Toluene, AQI, AQI_Bucket  
Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rohanrao/air-quality-data-in-india

